## Project Memory (ZSH) — Agent-Neutral

This project uses a **cross-agent, model-independent memory system**. On session start
or "continue previous work":

1. **Read `zsh/AGENT_MEMORY.md`** — sole entry point (memory map + read/write protocol).
2. Treat **`zsh/CURRENT_TASK.md`** as the authoritative persisted work state.
3. **Do not infer history** before reading the memory files. When this agent's native
   memory conflicts with ZSH project memory, **ZSH project memory wins** — keep the ZSH
   baseline and ask before overwriting.
4. At session end, follow the write-back protocol in `zsh/AGENT_MEMORY.md`
   (skip duplicates, confirm conflicts, reject secrets / absolute local paths).

Memory files: `zsh/{PROJECT_MEMORY,SESSION_LOG,DECISIONS}.md`
+ `zsh/memory-archive/INDEX.md` (weekly archives, read-only).

> ℹ️ Your native memory / this instruction file is **candidate-only**. ZSH project memory
> stores the verified authoritative facts.
